 1045
Your Honor,

I stand here today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I acknowledge and take full responsibility for my actions on the day in question.

On that day, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members. Regrettably, I allowed my impatience and the pressure of time to get the best of me, leading me to drive aggressively and exceed the speed limit. I also made the poor decision to read and respond to a text message while behind the wheel. As a consequence of my reckless behavior, I collided with a guardrail. Thankfully, there were no injuries sustained by anyone else involved.

In hindsight, I now fully comprehend the gravity of my actions. I wholeheartedly recognize the dangerous nature of my driving on that day, not only jeopardizing my own safety but also posing a risk to the well-being of others on the road. I am genuinely remorseful for the potential harm I could have caused.

Your Honor, I am 37 years old and have a clean record up until this incident. I understand that my prior speeding offense is a testament to my error in judgment and lack of regard for traffic regulations. I assure the court that I deeply regret my past actions and have since taken steps to better educate myself about the importance of adhering to road safety laws.

Furthermore, I would like to bring to your attention that I regularly contribute to the British Heart Foundation, an organization close to my heart. Through my financial donations, I aim to make a positive impact and give back to society.

In conclusion, I respectfully consider my guilty plea as a mitigating factor, acknowledging my accountability for the offense. I am fully prepared to accept the consequences of my actions and pledge to learn from this experience. I sincerely apologize for my careless driving and assure you, Your Honor, that such an incident will never happen again.

Thank you for considering my plea.

Yours sincerely,

Charlotte Porter

