Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I would like to express my regret and accept full responsibility for my actions.

Firstly, I would like to emphasize that I am pleading guilty to this offense, thereby acknowledging my wrongdoing and sparing the court the need for a trial. I understand that my guilty plea is an important mitigating factor that benefits the court.

On the day in question, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. Regrettably, I was running late and allowed my impatience to cloud my judgment while driving. I acknowledge that I was driving aggressively, exceeding the speed limit, and putting other road users at risk. Additionally, I made the grave mistake of using my phone to respond to a text message, taking my attention away from the road completely.

As a result of my reckless behavior, I collided with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was injured in the incident. I am deeply aware of how fortunate we were to escape any harm, and I am filled with remorse for the potential consequences that could have occurred due to my actions.

I want to assure the court that this incident does not reflect my overall character. I have realized the gravity of my actions and fully understand the importance of adhering to traffic regulations and the potential dangers of driving recklessly. Going forward, I am committed to becoming a more conscientious and law-abiding driver.

I apologize for any distress I may have caused, and I am ready to face the appropriate consequences for my actions. Your leniency and understanding are humbly requested, taking into consideration my guilty plea as a mitigating factor in this case.

Thank you for your consideration.

Yours sincerely,

Charlotte Porter
